      {
        "id": 4658,
        "name": "",
        "username": "jonahwest",
        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/j/90db22/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-15T05:33:39.045Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alexmiller\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"1519\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/48/326_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alexmiller:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You\u2019d still have one DC as the place where writes happen, and commits would go across it and another random DC.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I may be understanding this wrong, but could you please clarify this? I thought writes are spread evenly across the cluster even in <code>three_datacenter</code>.</p>",
